\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A.1}{\ignorespaces The memory storage of the matrix representation of the Hamiltonian Equation \ref {eq:spin_triplet_BdG_Hamiltonian} in \texttt {Python}'s \texttt {NumPy} library. Complex matrix entries are $16$ bytes and the size of the matrix depends on the number of sites $N=N_x=N_y$ as $\left (2^3\cdot N^2\right )^2$. Typical RAM capacity ($64$gb) limits us to $N=87$ ($58.7$gb). \relax }}{57}{figure.caption.37}%
